PORT OF SPAIN, Trinidad (AP) — The West Indies won the toss and made India bat first in their opening one-day international on Friday at the Queen’s Park Oval.The West Indies is coming off being swept 3-0 at home by Bangladesh in an ODI series, while India just beat host England 2-1.West Indies all-rounder Jason Holder won’t play in the first ODI after testing positive for COVID-19. Holder was back in the squad after missing the series against Bangladesh. Kyle Mayers returns from injury.India captain Shikhar Dhawan said he also would have bowled first. An under-strength India is resting players after the England series. All-rounder Ravindra Jadeja will miss the first two games of the three-match series because of a knee injury.___Lineups:West Indies: Shai Hope, Brandon King, Shamarh Brooks, Nicholas Pooran (captain), Rovman Powell, Akeal Hosein, Romario Shepherd, Kyle Mayers, Gudakesh Motie, Alzarri Joseph, Jayden Seales.India: Shikhar Dhawan (captain), Shubman Gill, Shreyas Iyer, Suryakumar Yadav, Sanju Samson, Deepak Hooda, Axar Patel, Shardul Thakur, Yuzvendra Chahal, Mohammed Siraj, Prasidh Krishna.___More AP cricket: https://apnews.com/hub/cricket and https://twitter.com/AP_Sports